The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 HSBC Investments has launched HSBC Capital Guard Portfolio under its portfolio management services business. The scheme guarantees capital investment by HSBC Bank plc, UK. It offers 100 per cent capital protection at maturity. An investor can choose up to 100 per cent equity exposure and a profit lock-in mechanism. The portfolio will have a four-year tenure. The investor will have an option to exit, subject to charges, before the maturity of the portfolio. The portfolio is open for subscription till July 20 and the minimum investment is Rs 25 lakh. The portfolio will not accept any fresh subscriptions after the launch.

 ICICI Lombard General Insurance Company has launched a personal accident plan, including cover for permanent total disablement, with three sum assured options. One can buy a policy for a sum assured of Rs 3 lakh, Rs 5 lakh or Rs 10 lakh for a term of three, four or five years. The premium for a cover of Rs 3 lakh for three years is Rs 1,125 or Rs 375 per annum. The insurer has also launched a personal accident plan for a sum assured of Rs 20 lakh. The premium for a three-year policy is Rs 16,000.

 Franklin Templeton has announced a tax-free dividend of Rs 6 per unit in its Franklin India Prima Fund. The record date is July 18.




